            As someone born in Bandung, I find this loss crushing. I wrote <span class="italic">Queers Shoot Back!</span> believing radical cinema came from elsewhere, unable to see how my own city incubated the first dream of Third World solidarity. This is the deep wound of 1965: not only bodies obliterated, but entire horizons of imagination exterminated.
          </p>

